article.headline: Cal St.-Fullerton 118, Redlands 68
article.story: FULLERTON, Calif. -- Sophomore Isiah Umipig scored 34 points to lead five players in double figures as Cal State Fullerton routed Redlands 118-68 Friday night in the Titans' season opener. Umipig scored 17 points in each half. He made eight of his 12 3-point tries and was 11 of 16 overall. D.J. Seeley scored 18 points, Omondi Amoke added 16 and Kwame Vaughn scored 12 in their first games as Titans. Seeley and Amoke transferred from Cal; Vaughn from San Francisco. Fullerton led 70-27 at the half. The 118 points are the second most in Fullerton history; the Titans scored 128 against Chapman in 1972. Jack Colston led Redlands with 14 points and Kirk Tristan added 13 points.
